Clive Woodward Couldn’t Work Part-Time in RFU Role, Chairman Says

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-06-12T12:50:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-12/clive-woodward-couldn-t-work-part-time-in-rfu-role-chairman-says.html
Rugby Football Union Chairman Martyn
Thomas said Clive Woodward would have to be fully committed and
leave his British Olympic Association post if he wanted to be
become performance director with the English rugby ruling body.  “We languish in sixth in the International Rugby Board
rankings, it’s unacceptable,” Thomas told BBC Radio 5 Live’s
Sportsweek program. “I don’t believe we can have a situation
where a part-timer is doing the job, even if he was to come at a
later stage. That for me would not be an answer.”  Woodward coached  England  to the Rugby World Cup title in
2003, and has been linked in media reports with the RFU role.
Last month he said he won’t be interviewed for the post and
pledged his commitment to the BOA, where he’s director of elite
performance.  John Steele was ousted as RFU chief executive last week
after confusion over the process of appointing the performance
director  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
